                     <interp inst="t16830524-1-off4" type="offenceSubcategory" value="highwayRobbery"></interp>
               Prosecutor traviling late, were in a lonely place, set upon by the Prisoner, &amp; three more of his accomplices, who carryed them into a Field adjoyning to the Road, and there riffled them, taking from the former, a Coat, a Sword, and a pair of Frienged Gloves, and from the latter his Coat, Sword, Belt, Rings, Buckles, and twelve Shillings in Mony
            </rs>. This being sworn, the Prisoner utterly deny'd the Fact, saying that he was at home in Bed at that time the robery was said to be done, but<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="16830524002"></xptr>not being able to prove it, not give any good account for himself, he was found <rs id="t16830524-1-verdict5" type="verdictDescription">
